Provide DNA sample, if not already done. Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered.
- Fine set at ZERO.
- Restitution set at ZERO.

- No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm magazine, firearm holster, or any body armor.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions: Firearm possession and Voting.

Court advises the defendant that under Wisconsin Statute 302.113 the amount actually served may be extended, and that the defendant could serve the entire bifurcated sentence in prison. The defendant will be subject to certain conditions while on release to ES, and a violation of any of those conditions may result in the defendant being returned to prison.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- No Contact with Angelica F. or any children of Angelica F. Only exception is during appearances at the Milwaukee County Juvenile Court Family Drug Treatment Program.
- No Contact with Malcolm H.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- Maintain Absolue Sobriety: No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.
- DOC's must conduct drug and alcohol testing.
- Defendant to notify DOC's agent of all prescriptions within 3 business days/72 hours of receiving prescription from medical professional.
- Fill all prescriptions at one pharmacy, unless otherwise approved by DOC's Agent, and notify the DOC's Agent of the pharmacy used.
- No possession of anydrug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.
- Maintain full time employment.
- Comply with all Children's Court and Bureau of Child Welfare Court orders.
- Mental Health Evaluation and any recommended treatment.
- Court recommends Trauma Informed Mental Health Treatment.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Samantha Lee Fiebrink in court with attorney Edward J. Hunt.  Patricia Irene Daugherty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: tmk.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.

AS TO COUNT 1-

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS 6 MONTHS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 5 days (5-31-2015 to 06-04-2015) time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR and 6 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION 
- No contact with Angelica F.  or any children of Angelica F. Only exception is during appearances at the Milwaukee County Juvenile Court Family Drug Treatment Program. 
- No contact with Malcolm H.
- Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS CONDITION TIME  in the House of Correction without goodtime credit; release for The Day Reporting Center,  inmate work assignments within the House of Correction, AODA treatment, for childcare for supervised visited with children according to any order for Children's Court or Bureau of Child Welfare, and attending any mandatory appearance in Children's Court. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring except if defendant is in a residential AODA program.  

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION AND CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- Maintain Absolute Sobriety: No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.  
- Department of Corrections must conduct drug and alcohol testing.
- Defendant to notify Department of Corrections agent of all prescriptions within 3 business days/72 hours of receiving prescription from medical professional.
- Fill all prescriptions at one pharmacy, unless otherwise approved by Department of Corrections Agent, and notify the Department of Corrections agent of the pharmacy used. 
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.
- No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm magazine, firearm holster, or any body armor.
- Maintain full time employment. 
- Comply with all Children's Court and Bureau of Child Welfare Court orders. 
- Mental Health Evaluation and any recommended treatment. 
- Court recommends Trauma Informed Mental Health Treatment. 
- Restitution set at ZERO. 
- Fine is set at ZERO.
- Drivers license suspension is not imposed.
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done. 
- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered. 

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.

The Court informed the defendant of requirements and penalties applicable under s. 941.29(1m) or (4m).

Court advises the Defendant that under Wisconsin Statute 302.113 the amount actually served may be extended, and that the Defendant could serve the entire bifurcated sentence in prison. The Defendant will be subject to certain conditions while on release to extended supervision, and a violation of any of those conditions may result in the Defendant being returned to prison. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 

Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
